with the renaming, this block now looks like this. If no caught up clients exist, we just assign it to the ClientState right away; otherwise, if and only if taskIsCaughtUpOnClientOrNoCaughtUpClientsExist returns false, do we add to taskMovements.
So by (I think it's called deMorgan's Law?):
!(caughtUpOnClient | noCaughtUpClientsExist)
== !caughtUpOnClient & !noCaughtUpClientsExist
== notCaughtUpOnClient & caughtUpClientsExist
∴ caught-up clients exist
I also feel like I might be missing your point, but I hope we can get somewhere when the method is more appropriately named 🙂

